                                    <h1>Transport Management System (TMS) Software Development Cost in India 2026 — Features, Modules &amp; Pricing</h1>

                                    <p>If you run a transportation business — a 3PL, a fleet operator, a freight forwarder, or a manufacturer with in-house logistics — you've probably outgrown spreadsheets, WhatsApp groups and the entry-level TMS modules bolted onto your accounting software. The next step is a <strong>custom Transport Management System (TMS)</strong> that owns route planning, dispatch, freight billing, customer portals and BI in one system. This 2026 guide covers what a real TMS includes, how Indian engineering studios price the build, and what to budget for ongoing operations. We've shipped TMS modules across our <a href='../products/courier-management-software.php'>courier management software</a> and <a href='../products/logistics-mobile-app.php'>logistics mobile app</a> stack — this guide is the playbook we hand to clients on day one.</p>

                                    <h2>TL;DR — TMS Software Cost in India 2026</h2>

                                    <ul><li><strong>Starter TMS</strong> (single fleet, basic dispatch + tracking + invoicing): &#8377;8L – &#8377;14L &middot; 6–10 weeks</li><li><strong>Growth TMS</strong> (multi-fleet, route optimisation, EDI, customer portal, mobile app): &#8377;18L – &#8377;30L &middot; 3–4 months</li><li><strong>Enterprise TMS</strong> (multi-country, ERP/SAP/Oracle integration, AI dispatch, BI): &#8377;40L – &#8377;90L+ &middot; 6–9 months</li></ul><p>The 5–7&times; spread is real. A 12-truck regional operator does not need the same TMS as a 1,200-truck national 3PL with SAP and EDI partners. Most of the cost lives in three places: <em>route optimisation, multi-stakeholder portals, and finance integration</em>.</p>

                                    <h2>Core Modules Every Real TMS Has in 2026</h2>

                                    <p>Anything missing more than two of these modules is a dispatch tool, not a TMS:</p><ol><li><strong>Order &amp; consignment management</strong> — bookings, manifests, multi-leg shipments, COD/non-COD, freight class.</li><li><strong>Route planning &amp; dispatch</strong> — auto-assignment, vehicle matching, multi-stop optimisation, surge pricing.</li><li><strong>Real-time tracking</strong> — driver app + GPS device telemetry, ETA calculation, geofencing alerts.</li><li><strong>Freight billing &amp; rating</strong> — slab/zone/weight rate engines, fuel surcharges, demurrage, multi-currency.</li><li><strong>Customer &amp; vendor portals</strong> — self-service booking, tracking, invoice download, dispute raising.</li><li><strong>Finance &amp; reconciliation</strong> — automated invoice generation, GST/VAT compliance, payable cycles, ageing reports.</li><li><strong>Compliance &amp; e-way bill</strong> — Indian e-way bill auto-push, FASTag reconciliation, EU e-CMR, US ELD-compatible logs.</li><li><strong>BI &amp; analytics</strong> — fleet utilisation, on-time%, cost-per-km, profitability per route.</li></ol>

                                    <h2>Build vs Buy — When a Custom TMS Is the Right Call</h2>

                                    <p>You should pick a SaaS TMS (Shipsy, FarEye, LogiNext, Track-POD) when:</p><ul><li>You operate &lt;30 vehicles and standard dispatch flows fit your business</li><li>You need to go live in 2–4 weeks</li><li>Your IT budget is &lt;&#8377;15L/yr including software + hardware</li></ul><p>You should build a custom TMS when:</p><ul><li>Your routing logic is non-standard (cold chain, hazmat, oversized loads, multi-modal)</li><li>You need deep ERP / SAP / Oracle / Tally integration with your existing finance stack</li><li>Your customers expect a branded portal under your domain</li><li>SaaS per-shipment pricing breaks ROI past 5,000 shipments/month</li><li>You want to license the platform back to peers or franchisees</li></ul>

                                    <h2>Module-by-Module Cost Breakdown (Growth-Tier TMS, ~&#8377;25L)</h2>

                                    <table style='width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:18px 0;'><thead><tr style='background:#fff1e6;'><th style='padding:10px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Module</th><th style='padding:10px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Hours</th><th style='padding:10px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Cost (&#8377;)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Discovery, BPMN, system design</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>100–140</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;1.8L – 2.4L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Order &amp; consignment management</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>200–260</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;3L – 4L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Route planning &amp; dispatch engine</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>240–320</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;3.6L – 4.8L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Driver mobile app (Android + iOS)</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>200–260</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;3L – 4L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Customer &amp; vendor self-service portal</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>160–220</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;2.4L – 3.3L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Billing, rating engine, e-way bill, GST</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>180–240</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;2.7L – 3.6L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>BI dashboards, exports, KPI alerts</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>120–160</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;1.8L – 2.4L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>QA, security, deployment, training</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>120–160</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;1.8L – 2.4L</td></tr></tbody></table>

                                    <h2>Integrations You Should Plan For Day One</h2>

                                    <p>The integrations are usually where TMS projects slip schedule. Plan these from kickoff:</p><ul><li><strong>FASTag &amp; e-way bill</strong> — IRP push for invoices, FASTag reconciliation API for highway tolls.</li><li><strong>GPS / IoT devices</strong> — Teltonika, Concox, Aplicom — most operators run a mixed fleet of devices.</li><li><strong>ERP / accounting</strong> — Tally, SAP B1 / S/4 HANA, Oracle NetSuite, Zoho Books, QuickBooks.</li><li><strong>Payment gateways</strong> — Razorpay / Stripe / PayU for prepaid customer payments and split payouts.</li><li><strong>SMS &amp; WhatsApp Cloud API</strong> — booking confirmations, ETAs, POD notifications.</li><li><strong>Maps &amp; routing</strong> — Google Maps, Mapbox, HERE Maps for distance + traffic-aware routing.</li><li><strong>Customer EDI</strong> — most enterprise shippers (auto, FMCG, retail) require EDI 204/210/214 messages.</li></ul>

                                    <h2>Hidden Costs in Years 1 and 2</h2>

                                    <p>Founders often budget the build and forget what comes after launch. Realistic year-1 + year-2 costs:</p><ul><li><strong>Cloud + DB (AWS / GCP):</strong> &#8377;25k–&#8377;1.2L/month based on shipment volume.</li><li><strong>Maps / routing API:</strong> &#8377;15k–&#8377;80k/month at scale; Mapbox cuts ~40% over Google.</li><li><strong>SMS / WhatsApp:</strong> &#8377;0.15–&#8377;0.50/message — at 50k shipments/month this is &#8377;30k+.</li><li><strong>L2 support &amp; bug fixes:</strong> 15–20% of build cost annually.</li><li><strong>Roadmap (new modules):</strong> budget another 30–40% of build cost across years 1+2.</li></ul><p>Total realistic year-1 cost of a custom TMS: <strong>build cost + 35–50%</strong>. Budget that from day one.</p>

                                    <h2>Why ITD GrowthLabs for Your TMS Build</h2>

                                    <p><strong>Why founders pick ITD GrowthLabs for logistics builds:</strong> 200+ logistics deployments, 50M+ shipments handled across our platforms, <a href='../products/courier-management-software.php'>a productised CMS</a> and <a href='../products/logistics-mobile-app.php'>a logistics mobile app suite</a> that cut 60–70% of the build time. You don't pay us to learn courier ops on your project — we already know hub manifests, COD reconciliation, scan exceptions and surge dispatch.</p>

