                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How long does it take to build a custom TMS in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>A Starter TMS ships in 6–10 weeks. A Growth-tier TMS with route optimisation, customer portal and driver app takes 3–4 months. Enterprise builds with ERP integration and multi-country support take 6–9 months. Most timeline slippage comes from delayed integration spec sign-off, not core development.</p>
                                        <h3>Should we build the TMS on cloud or on-premise?</h3>
                                        <p>Cloud (AWS / GCP / Azure) for ~95% of operators in 2026 — lower opex, easier scaling, better DR. On-prem only when your enterprise customers contractually require it (defence, classified-cargo) or when local data-residency law mandates it.</p>
                                        <h3>Will a custom TMS replace our SAP / Tally / ERP?</h3>
                                        <p>No — a TMS sits next to your ERP, not on top of it. Bookings, dispatch, tracking, and POD live in TMS; ledgers, P&amp;L, and master vendor data stay in ERP. The integration moves invoices and reconciliations between them via API or scheduled batch.</p>
                                        <h3>How do you handle e-way bill and GST automation?</h3>
                                        <p>We integrate with the IRP (Invoice Registration Portal) API and NIC e-way bill API directly from the TMS billing module. The system auto-generates IRN and EWB on consignment confirmation, with a manual override for edge cases. GST returns export to the format your CA imports into Tally / Zoho.</p>
                                        <h3>Do you give us full source-code ownership?</h3>
                                        <p>Yes. Every TMS we build is delivered as a work-for-hire contract with 100% source-code transfer to your private GitHub / Bitbucket. You can self-host, hire any vendor for future maintenance, or licence the platform onward.</p>
                                        <h3>What's the realistic ROI on a custom TMS?</h3>
                                        <p>Across our deployments, custom TMS users see 8–15% reduction in cost-per-shipment in year 1 (route optimisation + idle-fleet visibility), 15–25% reduction in dispute resolution time (POD automation), and 20–30% improvement in customer NPS (self-service tracking). Payback in 9–14 months for most growth-stage operators.</p>
